    "summary": "A lustrous, silvery-blue metal. It is magnetic. Cobalt is found in the minerals cobaltite, skutterudite and erythrite. Important ore deposits are found in DR Congo, Canada, Australia, Zambia and Brazil. Most cobalt is formed as a by-product of nickel refining. A huge reserve of several transition metals (including cobalt) can be found in strange nodules on the…",
