    "summary": "Cadmium is a silvery metal with a bluish tinge to its surface. The only mineral containing significant quantities of cadmium is greenockite (cadmium sulfide). It is also present in small amounts in sphalerite. Almost all commercially produced cadmium is obtained as a by-product of zinc refining.",
