    "summary": "A soft, silvery metal that is stable in air and water. Indium is one of the least abundant minerals on Earth. It has been found uncombined in nature, but typically it is found associated with zinc minerals and iron, lead and copper ores. It is commercially produced as a by-product of zinc refining.",
    "safety": "Bulk metal is generally more stable than powder; control dust, fumes, hot work, and compound-specific hazards.",
