    "summary": "Antimony is a semi-metal. In its metallic form it is silvery, hard and brittle. Antimony is not an abundant element but is found in small quantities in over 100 mineral species. It is most often found as antimony(III) sulfide. It is extracted by roasting the antimony(III) sulfide to the oxide, and then reducing with carbon. Antimony can also be found as the native metal. China produces 88% of the…",
